        "last_activity_date": 1279720408,
        "creation_date": 1279714895,
        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "How to match the last word in a sentence?",
        "body": "<p>Suppose we have <em>one<\/em> sentence (several words without a dot after the last one).<\/p>\n\n<p>I need to wrap the last word with some html tags (for example, <code>&lt;strong&gt;lastword&lt;/strong&gt;<\/code>).<\/p>\n\n<p>How can I achieve this with java regular expressions?<\/p>\n\n<p>I've already tried this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>\"John Doe Jr\".replaceAll (\"( .+$)\", \"&lt;strong&gt;$1&lt;/strong&gt;\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>but it results in <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>John&lt;strong&gt; Doe Jr&lt;/strong&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>p.s. It's ok if we have a whitespace after <code>&lt;strong&gt;<\/code>, the main problem is that the pattern matches the biggest subsequence while I need the smallest one.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 3299101,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "regex"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "accepted_answer_id": 3299214,
        "is_answered": true,
